From: LunaOS Project <lunaos@puredarwin.org>
Date: 2026-02-28
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] anv: Darwin stub — Intel Vulkan for future i915 KEXT

anv (Intel Vulkan) requires the i915 DRM kernel driver to be present.
On Darwin, i915 doesn't exist yet — it needs to be ported as a KEXT.

This patch makes anv compile on Darwin but:
  - Fails gracefully at vkCreateInstance if /dev/dri/renderD128 is not
    an i915 device (detected via DRM_IOCTL_VERSION checking driver name)
  - Logs a clear message: "anv: i915 KEXT not loaded — falling back to lavapipe"
  - Returns VK_ERROR_INCOMPATIBLE_DRIVER so the loader tries the next ICD

When the i915 KEXT is eventually ported:
  1. Build Mesa with -Dvulkan-drivers=...,intel
  2. Rename anv_icd.x86_64.json.disabled → anv_icd.x86_64.json
  3. anv will be discovered automatically by the Vulkan loader

TODO_i915_KEXT: Port the Linux i915 DRM driver as an x86_64 Darwin KEXT.
  Reference: https://github.com/torvalds/linux/tree/master/drivers/gpu/drm/i915
  PureDarwin issue: https://github.com/PureDarwin/PureDarwin/issues/TBD
---
diff --git a/src/intel/vulkan/anv_device.c b/src/intel/vulkan/anv_device.c
--- a/src/intel/vulkan/anv_device.c
+++ b/src/intel/vulkan/anv_device.c
@@ -1,5 +1,40 @@
 #include "anv_private.h"
 
+#ifdef MESA_DARWIN
+/*
+ * Darwin anv stub.
+ *
+ * We probe for i915 by opening /dev/dri/renderD128 and checking the
+ * DRM driver name via DRM_IOCTL_VERSION. If it's not "i915", we bail
+ * with VK_ERROR_INCOMPATIBLE_DRIVER so lavapipe handles the request.
+ *
+ * This stub allows anv to be compiled into the Mesa build and included
+ * in the ICD manifest search path, without breaking systems that don't
+ * have an Intel GPU or the i915 KEXT.
+ */
+#include <fcntl.h>
+#include <sys/ioctl.h>
+#include "drm_darwin.h"   /* from our darwin-wayland headers */
+
+static bool darwin_has_i915(void) {
+    int fd = open("/dev/dri/renderD128", O_RDWR | O_CLOEXEC);
+    if (fd < 0) return false;
+
+    char name_buf[64] = {};
+    struct drm_version ver = {
+        .name     = name_buf,
+        .name_len = sizeof(name_buf) - 1,
+    };
+    bool ok = (ioctl(fd, DRM_IOCTL_VERSION, &ver) == 0 &&
+               strncmp(name_buf, "i915", 4) == 0);
+    close(fd);
+    return ok;
+}
+
+/* Called at VkCreateInstance time */
+VkResult anv_darwin_check_device(void) {
+    if (!darwin_has_i915()) {
+        mesa_loge("anv: Intel i915 GPU not found. "
+                  "TODO_i915_KEXT: port i915 as a Darwin KEXT to enable "
+                  "hardware Intel Vulkan. Falling back to lavapipe.");
+        return VK_ERROR_INCOMPATIBLE_DRIVER;
+    }
+    return VK_SUCCESS;
+}
+#endif /* MESA_DARWIN */
